⁸ We are spreading our sails for blissful havens, in quest of great Siro’s wise words, and from all care will redeem our life. Get ye hence, ye Muses! yea, away now even with you, ye sweet Muses! For the truth we must avow——ye have been sweet. And yet, come ye back to my pages, though with modesty and but seldom. ¹
